comment: Yeah, it easier to win a liable/defamation/slander case in the UK. This is because in the US there is the "Westmoreland Rule" in which the plaintiff has to prove what was said or printed is false, and to make things more hard, if you are a piblic figure you have to prove actual malice. It's reveresed in the UK as the defendant has to prove that it's true, so it's much easier to win in the UK than the US.
